{
  "text": "For each positive integer d there is a natural operator which maps modular forms for \u03c1 N to forms for \u03c1 N d 2 (see [CITATION_1] , Section 4). Under the isomorphism J * k+1/2,N \u223c = M k,\u03c1 N it corresponds to the index raising operator U d defined in [CITATION_2] , Section 4. Its action on the Fourier expansion of a holomorphic modular form",
  "correct_citation": {
